[30;1m268 | [0m[35m    data in the background to reclaim storage space. This process is[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35m    known as "version GC". By default, version GC reclaims versions[0m
[30;1m270 | [0m[35m    after they are one hour old. Because of this, Cloud Spanner cannot[0m
[30;1m271 | [0m[35m    perform reads at read timestamps more than one hour in the past.[0m
[30;1m272 | [0m[35m    This restriction also applies to in-progress reads and/or SQL[0m
